headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 23 points, Steven Adams added 17 points and 14 rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies routed the Detroit Pistons 132-107 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Adams lead Grizzlies to 132-107 rout of Pistons

headlines.description: — In a matchup of teams that were transformed at the trade deadline, the Washington Wizards got an immediate boost from improved chemistry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma leads Wizards past Irving, in-flux Nets, 113-112

events.name: Miami Heat at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored a season-high 42 points, and the Toronto Raptors pushed their season-high winning streak to eight games with a 139-120 victory over the Houston Rockets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent has 42; Raptors push streak to 8 with win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic says he will miss Kristaps Porzingis after the Dallas Mavericks traded the player who never quite measured up as the European sidekick to the team's young superstar.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 28 in 1st, 51 total, Mavs top Clippers 112-105

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson eased past his defender and slammed home a pretty one-handed dunk, thrilling a sellout crowd and giving the Phoenix Suns a 20-point cushion heading into the fourth quarter of a 131-107 win over the Milwaukee Bucks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns top Bucks 131-107 in rematch of last year's NBA Finals

events.name: New York Knicks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 28 points and matched his season high of 16 rebounds, and the New York Knicks earned their first win in four tries during their West Coast trip, holding off the Golden State Warriors 116-114 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks earn first win of trip, hold off Warriors
